<bibRefCitation id="EFBC4B61FF8CFF89C4A4ABD6FB59FE13" author="Cerny, K. &amp; Pinratana, A." box="[896,1162,441,467]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" refId="ref2079" refString="Cerny, K. &amp; Pinratana, A. (2009) Moths of Thailand, Vol. 6, Arctiidae. Brothers of Saint Gabriel in Thailand, Bangkok, 283 pp." type="book" year="2009">Černy &amp; Pinratana 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC4B61FF8CFF89C3B1ABD4FA9BFE13" author="Dubatolov, V. V." box="[1173,1352,443,467]" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" pagination="1 - 106" refId="ref2227" refString="Dubatolov, V. V. (2010) Tiger moths of Eurasia (Lepidoptera: Arctiinae). Neue entomologische Nachrichten, 65, 1 - 106." type="journal article" year="2010">Dubatolov 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Exter- nally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D13FF8CFF89C7FDAB8FFEA1FE37" authorityName="Saldaitis, Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov" authorityYear="2020" box="[217,370,479,503]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persephone">
<emphasis id="B959EA82FF8CFF89C7FDAB8FFEA1FE37" box="[217,370,479,503]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">L. persephone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13162A15FF8CFF89C6A5ABB0FE31FE37" box="[385,482,479,503]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,1033,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[182,1404,1030,1949]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Lemyra spp., adults. 1, L. persephone, holotype ♂, China,Yunnan (ASV/WIGJ); 2, L. persephone, paratype ♂, China, Yunnan (AFM); 3, L. melanosoma, ♂, NE India (MWM/ZSM); 4, L. melanosoma, ♂, China, Yunnan (AFM)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784032" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3784032/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) is very different from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D13FF8CFF89C5C7AB8FFC54FE37" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[739,903,479,503]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanosoma">
<emphasis id="B959EA82FF8CFF89C5C7AB8FFC54FE37" box="[739,903,479,503]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">L. melanosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13162A15FF8CFF89C4B2ABB0FC2BFE37" box="[918,1016,479,503]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[191,1395,1033,1946]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[182,1404,1030,1949]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Lemyra spp., adults. 1, L. persephone, holotype ♂, China,Yunnan (ASV/WIGJ); 2, L. persephone, paratype ♂, China, Yunnan (AFM); 3, L. melanosoma, ♂, NE India (MWM/ZSM); 4, L. melanosoma, ♂, China, Yunnan (AFM)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784032" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3784032/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
) and can be easily distinguished by its forewing with less elongated apex and strong lead gray suffusion on both wings, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D13FF8CFF89C348A86BFADCFDDB" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[1132,1295,515,539]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanosoma">
<emphasis id="B959EA82FF8CFF89C348A86BFADCFDDB" box="[1132,1295,515,539]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">L. melanosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the forewing apex is slightly more elongated and both wings are pure white or with very weak small diffuse spots in the discal cells. Despite the strong external differences, male genitalia of the two species are very similar. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D13FF8CFF89C3E3A823FA8CFDA3" authorityName="Saldaitis, Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov" authorityYear="2020" box="[1223,1375,587,611]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persephone">
<emphasis id="B959EA82FF8CFF89C3E3A823FA8CFDA3" box="[1223,1375,587,611]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">L. persephone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13162A15FF8CFF89C249A824FF12FD47" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1934,1956]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,187,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,182,1907]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Lemyra spp., male genitalia. 5, L. persephone, holotype, China, Yunnan, slide AV4756 Volynkin; 2, L. persephone, paratype, China, Yunnan, slide AV4755 Volynkin; 3, L. melanosoma, NE India, slide ZSM Arct. 2019-198; 4, L. melanosoma, China, Yunnan, slide AV5582 Volynkin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784034" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3784034/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
) differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D13FF8CFF89C67EA81FFE2DFD47" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[346,510,623,647]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanosoma">
<emphasis id="B959EA82FF8CFF89C67EA81FFE2DFD47" box="[346,510,623,647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">L. melanosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13162A15FF8CFF89C529A800FDBEFD47" box="[525,621,623,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1934,1956]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,187,1894]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[156,1430,182,1907]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Lemyra spp., male genitalia. 5, L. persephone, holotype, China, Yunnan, slide AV4756 Volynkin; 2, L. persephone, paratype, China, Yunnan, slide AV4755 Volynkin; 3, L. melanosoma, NE India, slide ZSM Arct. 2019-198; 4, L. melanosoma, China, Yunnan, slide AV5582 Volynkin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3784034" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3784034/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">Figs 7, 8</figureCitation>
) by its slightly broader tegumen, slightly more elongated juxta, more elongated distal section of valva (1.16–1.25 times longer), more massive aedeagus (length to width ratio is 5.3 contra 5.6–6.6 in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D13FF8CFF89C797A8D7FE84FD0F" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[179,343,695,719]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanosoma">
<emphasis id="B959EA82FF8CFF89C797A8D7FE84FD0F" box="[179,343,695,719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">L. melanosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and aedeagus vesica with slightly broader smaller cluster of spinules and broader larger cluster with strongly broadened basal section (that is not broadened in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D13FF8CFF89C420A8B3FC7BFD33" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[772,936,731,755]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Lemyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanosoma">
<emphasis id="B959EA82FF8CFF89C420A8B3FC7BFD33" box="[772,936,731,755]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="447">L. melanosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C337651BFF8CFF8BC7E3A890FE54FE4A" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="449" pageId="1" pageNumber="447" type="description">
